      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m ok with this, but adding a constructor to a type that didn\u0027t have one before can sometimes be a dicey thing.  If we\u0027ve been allocating these in ways that don\u0027t call the constructor, these fImage and fPathData pointers may still be uninitialized.\n\nIt may be safer and a stronger guarantee about initialization if you set these to nullptr in the existing init routines... is that just initWithGlyphID() now?",
      "revId": "64c92fca8df41d6d5961942c6a9bc074ff16ade9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
